
=Contacts=

Eunho Chun, Chief Researcher of Community Asset-Building Facilitation at Institute of Land and Liberty. His master thesis introduced the CLT model to Korean academia in the field of urban planning and public administration for the first time. <unochun@gmail.com> His interests center on community ownership, community asset transfer, community regeneration and sustainable value creation-and-investment in local communities. 

Dae-uk Jeon, Chief Researcher at Korea Research Institute For Local Administration. He's been closely involved in the process of legislating "Community Revitalisation Act" www.lawmaking.go.kr/lmSts/nsmLmSts/out/detailR?gnb=5&pageIndex=2&listKnd=nasb&snb=1&lawb_seq=2005796 , which is like Localism Bill in England. Dae Uk Jeon <dujeon@krila.re.kr>

